Abia Warriors Football Club of Umuahia continued their preparations for the resumption of the Nigeria Professional Football League with a 4-0 drubbing of Manga Football Academy, Owerri, in a friendly decided at the Umuahia Township Stadium today,National Daily learnt.
Williams Nmesirionye scored twice for the Warriors in the first half after Amos Ogbuagu had raised the curtains.
Second half substitute, Kola Raimi rounded off the scoring a few minutes after he was introduced in the second stanza,National Daily gathered.
